00:02:44.210 --> 00:02:46.070
and then our college
admissions tests

00:02:46.070 --> 00:02:48.230
kind of compound these
problems of inequity

00:02:48.230 --> 00:02:49.500
throughout the system.

00:02:49.500 --> 00:02:51.680
So if you're in a poor
district when you start out

00:02:51.680 --> 00:02:54.050
in kindergarten
through fifth grade,

00:02:54.050 --> 00:02:57.170
you continue on to a mediocre
or poor middle school,

00:02:57.170 --> 00:02:59.060
and then a mediocre
or poor high school,

00:02:59.060 --> 00:03:01.070
your chances of getting
into a great college

00:03:01.070 --> 00:03:02.672
